<br>
<br>
<br>
Calonderiel  :  kal-on-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>derry</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-ell<br>
<br>
Fierenduil  :    fee-air-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>en</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-doo-ill<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">(I realise the 'derry' part should really be split into 2 syllables, but it's easier to convey in text that way. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
Most definitely <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">not</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> 'kal-AAAWWWWWWNNN-dree-uhll' as I've heard it pronounced, which puts a horrible drawling emphasis (like the 'a' in American 'law') on the wrong syllable and omits another syllable altogether. The intention was for the sound to reflect the elven nature: delicate, light, graceful.<br>
<br>
If you really want to get technical, the r's are <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">lightly</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> rolled -- breath-ed, almost (<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>breath</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->-ed rather than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>breathed</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->) -- ummmm... as per Legolas' pronunciation of the 'r' in &quot;Aragorn&quot; or 'Galadriel' in the LOTR films, for example, as opposed to Gimli's heavily rolled r's. (Heavily rolled arse? What?) The 'doo' is not 'dyoo' or 'joo' -- again to keep the light, graceful sound.<br>
<br>
<br>
That said, the first name is entirely plagiarised from my favourite series of books, so the pronunciation is really just my interpretation. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The surname, Fierenduil, is a custom conglomeration of EQ <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(Fier'Dal)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and and generalised Tolkien-ism <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(think 'Thranduil', father of a certain Legolas Greenleaf)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*realises he put far too much thought and care into the creation and pronunciation of a name that people are only ever going <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">read</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->!!*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
